Definition.WordDefinition: Fourteen \Four"teen`\, a. [OE. fourtene, feowertene, AS. fe['o]wert[=y]ne, fe['o]wert[=e]ne. See {Four}, and {Ten}, and cf. {Forty}.] Four and ten more; twice seven. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition:
Fourteen \Four"teen`\, n. 1. The sum of ten and four; forteen units or objects. [1913 Webster]
2. A symbol representing fourteen, as 14 or xiv. [1913 Webster]
fourteen adj : being one more than thirteen [syn: {14}, {xiv}] n : the cardinal number that is the sum of thirteen and one [syn: {14}, {XIV}]
